Name: MICRONESIAN
HomelandData: Archeological evidence about the provenance of Micronesian speakers is vague, but it suggests they came from the south (i.e. From the Solomons, Vanuatu or the Fiji/west polynesian region. [...] It seems that most of Micronesia was settled about two thousand years ago.
